article.headline: Colorado State 70, Northern Colorado 57
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. (AP) -- Jason Smith had a game-high 26 points to go with nine rebounds and seven blocks as Colorado State defeated independent Northern Colorado 70-57 Friday night. Smith scored 20 of his points on 7-for-7 shooting in the second half as Colorado State (1-0) overcame a cold shooting first half. Michael Harrison added 15 points and 11 rebounds for Colorado State and the 100th meeting between the two schools -- the first in Greeley since Dec. 1, 1956. Colorado State leads the series 64-36. Matt Kline led Northern Colorado (0-1) with 15 points and Sean Taibi had 14. The Bears are in their second year in Division I. Northern Colorado remained close, pulling to within 45-44 with 8:55 left in the game before Smith took over. Smith scored eight points, including two free throws on a double technical on Cory Lewis and Kirk Archibeque over the next 2½ minutes to give Colorado a 54-46 cushion. Northern Colorado never got closer than six points over the last 6:11.
